access points are connected to specific things in a bucket for a SPECIFIC group of users - it uses R/W policies
access points simplify security management for s3 buckets
each access point has:
  its own DNS name
  an access point policy- manage security at scale

---

VPC origin

we can define the access point to be accessible only from within the VPC
you must create a VPC endpoint to access the access point
the vpc endpoint policy must allow access to the target bucket and access points
